When you’re holding a knife, _don’t grip_ it _too tightly_. Many people form a _tight fist_ around the hilt of the blade. Short term, this will make _slicing difficult_. And long term, it will _hurt your wrist_.

Instead, start by making a _Spider-Man hand_. You know how Spidey presses his _middle and ring fingers_ against his _palm_ to shoot webs? That’s how you should hold a knife. The _pressure_ should be between those _two fingers_ and your _palm_.

