Let’s _feel the difference_ between a _“fluid”_ vs. a _stiff grip_. Try _picking up_ your knife with _all your fingers_ curled around the _handle’s centre_. Make a little _chopping motion_ and look at the blade. Now _slowly release_ your _pinky finger_, _index finger_ and _thumb_. _Maintaining_ the grip with your remaining two fingers and palm, _relax_ your _wrist_. Make that _chopping motion_ again and see how the _blade moves fluidly_ instead of stiffly. _Feel_ how the knife is _safely_ in your _control_, but it’s _not rigid_.

<video class='img-fluid' autoplay controls playsinline loop muted poster='/assets/videos/lessons/knife-skills/grip-tutorial.png'>
  <source src='/assets/videos/lessons/knife-skills/grip-tutorial.webm' type='video/webm; codecs=vp9,vorbis'>
  <source src='/assets/videos/lessons/knife-skills/grip-tutorial.mp4' type='video/mp4'>
</video>

Next, with the _hilt_ still held between your _palm_, _ring_ and _middle fingers_, _pinch the blade_ with your _index finger_ and _thumb_ while your _pinky finger_ just _dangles_. Do you _feel_ that? That’s _control_. The _blade_, slightly _loose_ in your grip, is suddenly _stabilized_.

_Congratulations!_ You are now holding a knife properly.

And now more bad news: this isn’t one of those lessons that you master right away; this _will not_ even _feel natural_ at first, in part because you have likely been holding a knife wrong all your life. We will need to _practice_ to move this knowledge from our short term to long term memory. It takes _a lot of repetition_ for the conscious act to become a _routine_, _subconscious behaviour_ we engage in _without thinking_.

You may find yourself _forgetting_ or _lapsing_ into _bad knife habits_. This is _okay_, and is part of the _learning process_; just _notice_ the difference, _correct_ your form, and _move on_ with the prep. But, like many physical skills, this is _not pointless formality_. If you’ve ever worked out with weights, you know that _bad form_ can result in _injury_ (not to mention _wasted energy_). It’s the same with knife skills. So _be mindful_ of your grip.
